# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation - Already Complete

## Summary
Upon investigation, Vercel Speed Insights has already been successfully implemented in this project. The implementation was completed in commit `bbeb7bc` ("Enable Vercel Speed Insights tracking") and merged via pull request #6.

## Current Implementation Status
✅ **COMPLETE** - Speed Insights is properly configured for the HTML framework

## Implementation Details

### Framework Type
This is a static HTML site with Vercel serverless functions, so the HTML implementation approach was used.

### Files Modified (Previously)
- `public/index.html` - Added Speed Insights scripts before closing `</body>` tag

### Implementation Specifics
The following two scripts were added to `public/index.html` at lines 1941-1944:

```html
<script>
  window.si = window.si || function () { (window.siq = window.siq || []).push(arguments); };
</script>
<script defer src="/_vercel/speed-insights/script.js"></script>
```

### Configuration
- `vercel.json` already includes routes for `/_vercel/*` which properly handles Speed Insights endpoints
- No package installation was needed (as per HTML implementation guidelines)
- Scripts are correctly placed before the closing `</body>` tag

## Verification
- ✅ Initialization script (`window.si`) present at line 1942-1943
